This feature allows to define the ordered hierarchical structure required for the Flat File Writer component to write the output flat file.

> Note

The data schema must contain a single **Root element**. Each Root element may contain one or more **elements**. In turn, elements may contain other cascading elements. All elements may be further characterized by **attributes**. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

The icon next to each structure component indicates its type:

**Icon**

**Type**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Document root**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Element**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Attribute**

> Tip

In order to generate the output file correctly, you need to define the following key nodes and attributes in the output structure that the Flat File Writer will produce; in particular:

- **Document root**, containing all the elements in the structure

## Managing elements and attributes of the data structure
- Open the Flat File Writer's resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources)[.](#)

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Adding an element to the structure
This feature allows to add an element at the same level as an existing element in the ordered hierarchical structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Add element**. A new element is added to the structure; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Schema **tab, configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Node name**

Name of the new element

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the element can contain

**Type**

Select the element's type from the list. The available options are:

**builtin:string **(default) 

- **builtin:int **

- **builtin:date **

- **builtin:boolean **

- **builtin:binary**

> Important

In the DT3 UI, it is not possible to define custom types. To do so, switch to Classic Mode.

**Min occurrences**

Minimum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

When set to **0**, the attribute is optional.

To set the parameter as optional, you may also select the **Optional **checkbox.

**Max occurrences**

Maximum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

If there is no limit to the number of occurrences, select the **Unbounded **checkbox.

**Default value**

Default value to assign to the element

- Configure the required parameters in the **Settings **and **Values **tabs, as described in:

[DT3 Flat File Writer - Settings tab](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-writer-settings-tab)

- [DT3 Flat File Writer - Values tab](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-flat-file-writer-values-tab)

### Adding a child element to the structure
This feature allows to add a child element under an existing element in the ordered hierarchical structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Add child element**. A new element is added to the structure, hierarchically nested under the selected element; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Schema **tab, configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Node name**

Name of the new element

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the element can contain

**Type**

Select the element's type from the list. The available options are:

**builtin:string **(default) 

- **builtin:int **

- **builtin:date**

- **builtin:boolean**

- **builtin:binary**

> Important

In the DT3 UI, it is not possible to define custom types. To do so, switch to Classic Mode.

**Min occurrences**

Minimum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

When set to **0**, the attribute is optional.

To set the parameter as optional, you may also select the **Optional **checkbox.

**Max occurrences**

Maximum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

If there is no limit to the number of occurrences, select the **Unbounded **checkbox.

**Default value**

Default value to assign to the element

- Configure the required parameters in the **Settings **and **Values **tabs, as described in:

[DT3 Flat File Writer - Settings tab](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-flat-file-writer-settings-tab)

- [DT3 Flat File Writer - Values tab](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-flat-file-writer-values-tab)

### Adding an attribute to the structure
This feature allows to add an attribute to an element of the ordered hierarchical structure.

The functionality is useful, for example, when you want to define the properties or characteristics of an element of the structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Add attribute**. A new attribute is added to the structure, hierarchically nested under the selected element; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Schema **tab, configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Node name**

Name of the new attribute

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the attribute can contain

**Type**

Select the element's type from the list. The available options are:

**builtin:string **(default)

- **builtin:int **

- **builtin:date **

- **builtin:boolean **

- **builtin:binary**

**Mandatory**

Select this option to indicate that the attribute is mandatory.

**Default value**

Default value to assign to the attribute

- Configure the required parameters in the **Settings **and **Values **tabs, as described in:

[DT3 Flat File Writer - Settings tab](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-flat-file-writer-settings-tab)

- [DT3 Flat File Writer - Values tab](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-flat-file-writer-values-tab)

## Editing an element or attribute
This feature allows to view and edit the configuration details of the selected element or attribute.

- Click on the name of an element or attribute to view its details; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Edit the required fields, as described in the relevant sections above:

[Adding an element to the structure](/doxee-platform/docs/1-dt3-flat-file-writer-configuring-the-output-data-structure#adding-an-element-to-the-structure)

- [Adding an attribute to the structure](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-xml-reader-configuring-the-input-data-structure)

### Selecting the Document root
This feature allows to select the Document root within the ordered hierarchical structure of the output schema.

The functionality is essential as it allows to indicate the document entity within the output file produced by the Flat File Writer.

> Note

The Document root contains all the elements in the structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select **Set as Document root**. The selected element is now highlighted with the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon; for example:
